that attracted Elizabeth to him.

275
00:24:51.049 --> 00:24:52.801
Darcy's attitude was
rude and mocking.

276
00:24:52.884 --> 00:24:54.511
I think that he was lucky
to be with a woman...

277
00:24:54.594 --> 00:24:56.429
with as much integrity
as Elizabeth.

278
00:24:56.554 --> 00:24:58.389
The only reason he even
asked her to marry him...

279
00:24:58.515 --> 00:25:00.475
was 'cause she wouldn't
stop throwing herself...

280
00:25:00.558 --> 00:25:02.727
Throwing herself at him?
He was pursuing her.

281
00:25:02.811 --> 00:25:04.521
She's clearly not
satisfied with her life...

282
00:25:04.604 --> 00:25:06.648
and is looking for excitement
wherever she can get it.

283
00:25:06.731 --> 00:25:08.983
Well, I think that it's
obviously all in his head...

284
00:25:09.067 --> 00:25:11.361
that she had any
feelings for him at all.

285
00:25:11.444 --> 00:25:14.197
Well, there you have it.

286
00:25:16.199 --> 00:25:19.661
That's the power of a good book.

287
00:25:24.290 --> 00:25:26.084
That was exciting.

288
00:25:26.167 --> 00:25:28.545
No, it was annoying.

289
00:25:28.628 --> 00:25:29.712
I enjoyed it.

290
00:25:29.796 --> 00:25:31.881
Look, whatever you're
thinking, don't.

291
00:25:31.965 --> 00:25:34.926
