- Hm?

345
00:31:51.803 --> 00:31:54.597
What are... what are you doing?

346
00:31:54.723 --> 00:31:56.057
I'm going swimming.

347
00:31:59.894 --> 00:32:01.771
Hardin...

348
00:32:07.944 --> 00:32:08.820
Hardin.

349
00:32:12.157 --> 00:32:13.158
Come in.

350
00:32:15.827 --> 00:32:17.662
You can wear my t-shirt.

351
00:32:22.125 --> 00:32:23.835
It feels amazing.

352
00:32:36.890 --> 00:32:40.351
A little privacy, please?

353
00:32:50.945 --> 00:32:52.322
Okay.

354
00:32:58.119 --> 00:32:59.037
What?

355
00:33:02.207 --> 00:33:04.209
I like it better on you.

356
00:33:44.916 --> 00:33:47.168
Can I ask you something?

357
00:33:47.252 --> 00:33:49.087
Do I even have a choice?

358
00:33:52.090 --> 00:33:56.594
Who do you love the
most in the world?

359
00:33:56.678 --> 00:33:59.931
Easy... myself.

360
00:34:02.767 --> 00:34:04.728
Of course, you do.

361
00:34:07.147 --> 00:34:09.566
What's your boyfriend's name?

362
00:34:09.649 --> 00:34:11.192
It's Noah.

363
00:34:11.276 --> 00:34:15.613
Noah... does he go here?

364
00:34:15.697 --> 00:34:17.449
He's in high school.

365
00:34:17.532 --> 00:34:20.201
High school?

366
00:34:20.285 --> 00:34:23.621
And what does a high school
kid do to deserve you?

367
00:34:23.705 --> 00:34:26.291
He is nice to me.

368
00:34:26.374 --> 00:34:28.126
Nice?

369
00:34:29.753 --> 00:34:32.464
Isn't that just another
word for boring?

370
00:34:34.632 --> 00:34:36.760
Not always.

371
00:34:36.843 --> 00:34:39.804
Can I show you something?

372
00:34:43.266 --> 00:34:45.101
Hold your breath.

373
00:35:04.496 --> 00:35:09.000
Silence... it's peaceful.

374
00:35:12.045 --> 00:35:14.047
You think that's weird?

375
00:35:15.799 --> 00:35:19.260
No... not at all.

376
00:36:00.343 --> 00:36:04.514
I thought that you just
wanted to be friends.

377
00:36:08.935 --> 00:36:11.479
I don't think we can
ever be just friends.

378
00:38:10.223 --> 00:38:12.684
Have you never been
touched before?

379
00:38:27.490 --> 00:38:29.325
Why'd you stop?

380
00:38:32.787 --> 00:38:35.081
We've got time.

381
00:38:40.211 --> 00:38:42.046
So, why do you
call them "chips"?

382
00:38:42.172 --> 00:38:44.048
Why do you call them "fries"?

383
00:38:44.132 --> 00:38:45.008
Because they're fried.

384
00:38:45.133 --> 00:38:47.969
They're not French.

385
00:38:48.053 --> 00:38:51.556
You've got plenty there.

386
00:38:51.681 --> 00:38:53.725
Hey, uh, I ordered
mine without ketchup.

387
00:38:53.850 --> 00:38:54.893
Oh, right, I'll be right back.

388
00:38:54.976 --> 00:38:57.103
Thank you.

389
00:38:57.228 --> 00:39:00.732
No ketchup?
That's very un-American.

390
00:39:00.857 --> 00:39:02.609
I'm full of surprises.

391
00:39:05.737 --> 00:39:08.823
So... what's your story then?

392
00:39:08.907 --> 00:39:10.325
My story?

393
00:39:11.367 --> 00:39:16.623
Yeah. Like, your family?
How you ended up here?

394
00:39:16.706 --> 00:39:18.416
Pass.

395
00:39:21.711 --> 00:39:25.715
I just don't think asking a
bunch of arbitrary questions...

396
00:39:25.840 --> 00:39:29.928
about someone's past is really
gonna tell you who they are.

397
00:39:30.011 --> 00:39:33.098
I can find out who you
are by sitting here...

398
00:39:33.223 --> 00:39:35.100
and spending time with you.

399
00:39:42.482 --> 00:39:43.525
What?

400
00:39:45.026 --> 00:39:46.778
What?

401
00:39:46.861 --> 00:39:49.155
What are you doing?

402
00:39:49.280 --> 00:39:52.283
I'm just waiting for you to
reveal your true self to me...

403
00:39:52.367 --> 00:39:55.745
by just sitting here and
spending time with you.

404
00:39:55.829 --> 00:39:56.913
Here you go.

405
00:39:56.996 --> 00:39:59.416
Thank you.

406
00:39:59.499 --> 00:40:03.628
Okay, fair enough...
one question.

407
00:40:06.297 --> 00:40:08.007
Why do you have all
those romance novels...

408
00:40:08.133 --> 00:40:09.676
if you don't believe in love?

409
00:40:09.801 --> 00:40:11.344
Who says I don't
believe in love?

410
00:40:12.262 --> 00:40:15.140
You did, in Soto's class.

411
00:40:17.642 --> 00:40:19.060
True.

412
00:40:21.187 --> 00:40:24.315
Maybe don't believe
everything I say then.

413
00:40:25.316 --> 00:40:26.693
Oh, hey, guys.

414
00:40:28.820 --> 00:40:30.238
Hey, Tessa.

415
00:40:32.490 --> 00:40:37.078
Guys, let's just hang
out for a minute.

416
00:40:37.162 --> 00:40:39.789
So... what have
you two been up to?

417
00:40:39.873 --> 00:40:42.792
- We were just...
- We're just getting some food.

418
00:40:42.876 --> 00:40:45.837
Oh, how's the boyfriend, Tess?

419
00:40:45.962 --> 00:40:47.839
We're leaving.

420
00:40:47.922 --> 00:40:49.382
Perfect. I need a ride.

421
00:40:49.466 --> 00:40:52.135
It's not a good time, you
can ask Zed for a ride.

422
00:40:52.218 --> 00:40:53.845
Dude, we literally
just got here.

423
00:40:53.970 --> 00:40:55.055
Excuse me.

424
00:40:55.180 --> 00:40:56.181
You're excused.

425
00:40:59.267 --> 00:41:03.563
All right... Tessa?

426
00:41:04.064 --> 00:41:05.774
Really?

427
00:41:08.359 --> 00:41:11.112
Yes, I won't be long.

428
00:41:19.704 --> 00:41:20.914
I'll be at the bar.

429
00:41:21.039 --> 00:41:22.874
See you around.

430
00:41:26.878 --> 00:41:27.921
What's up, bro?

431
00:41:28.046 --> 00:41:29.631
So, fill us in.

432
00:41:35.595 --> 00:41:38.390
- What was that?
- What was what?

433
00:41:38.473 --> 00:41:41.476
Were you like embarrassed
that they saw us together?

434
00:41:41.559 --> 00:41:43.395
No.

435
00:41:47.690 --> 00:41:50.360
You know, I'm going to tell
Noah about us, I just...

436
00:41:50.485 --> 00:41:56.199
Us? What do you mean "us"?

437
00:41:56.282 --> 00:41:58.868
If you want to dump Mr. High
School, then go ahead...

438
00:41:58.952 --> 00:42:00.245
but don't do it on my account.

439
00:42:03.456 --> 00:42:04.499
What?

440
00:42:06.418 --> 00:42:09.671
Look, it was fun,
but I don't date.

441
00:42:16.094 --> 00:42:20.682
Are you actually kidding me?

442
00:43:59.239 --> 00:44:00.532
You're here.

443
00:44:20.218 --> 00:44:22.137
What are you dreaming about?

444
00:44:36.901 --> 00:44:38.903
Surprise!

445
00:44:38.987 --> 00:44:44.492
What... what are you...
what are you doing here?

446
00:44:46.286 --> 00:44:48.830
How are you?

447
00:44:50.915 --> 00:44:52.667
Thank you.

448
00:44:54.294 --> 00:44:56.421
Are you okay?

449
00:44:56.546 --> 00:44:59.132
Yeah. No, yeah, yeah, of course.

450
00:44:59.215 --> 00:45:00.592
- Okay.
- Thank you.

451
00:45:00.717 --> 00:45:01.593
Yeah.

452
00:45:02.552 --> 00:45:03.887
So, what are we gonna do?

453
00:45:18.276 --> 00:45:20.070
Hey,
there's Tessa.

454
00:45:20.153 --> 00:45:21.237
What's
up, Tessa?

455
00:45:21.321 --> 00:45:22.447
Hey.

456
00:45:23.823 --> 00:45:27.160
Hi.
We met at the dorm.

457
00:45:27.243 --> 00:45:29.370
- So, he does exist.
- Nice to meet you.

458
00:45:29.454 --> 00:45:30.497
What's up, man, it's
Zed, how's it going?

459
00:45:30.622 --> 00:45:31.623
