00:55:01.818 --> 00:55:02.986
Tessa...

530
00:55:03.069 --> 00:55:05.655
Go home, Hardin.

531
00:55:27.677 --> 00:55:31.723
Noah and I just broke up.

532
00:55:34.267 --> 00:55:37.395
I feel like I just
lost my best friend.

533
00:55:40.231 --> 00:55:42.484
Come over here.

534
00:57:10.822 --> 00:57:12.741
I didn't expect to see you.

535
00:57:23.501 --> 00:57:29.132
When my dad left, I was 10.

536
00:57:33.344 --> 00:57:37.265
He left us with nothing.

537
00:57:40.143 --> 00:57:46.107
And my mom, she just
sort of fell apart.

538
00:57:49.110 --> 00:57:51.988
I had to take
care of her alone

539
00:57:52.113 --> 00:57:56.117
but Noah was there
for me, you know?

540
00:57:59.537 --> 00:58:02.373
I hate myself for
what I did to him.

541
00:58:03.833 --> 00:58:06.878
Tessa, it's not your fault.

542
00:58:07.003 --> 00:58:09.839
Yeah, it is.

543
00:58:15.720 --> 00:58:18.181
Noah's my best friend.

544
00:58:22.477 --> 00:58:24.229
But you...

545
00:58:30.402 --> 00:58:32.404
You're so much more.

546
00:58:42.205 --> 00:58:43.581
Library is closing.

547
00:58:43.665 --> 00:58:45.917
Library is
getting ready to close.

548
00:58:46.418 --> 00:58:47.919
Library is closing!

549
00:58:51.047 --> 00:58:53.049
- Follow me.
- Hm?

550
00:58:53.174 --> 00:58:54.592
- Come on.
- What are...

551
00:58:54.718 --> 00:58:56.386
Down here.

552
00:58:59.055 --> 00:59:01.224
Ssh.

553
00:59:12.110 --> 00:59:16.281
"You could draw me to fire.
You could draw me to water.

554
00:59:16.364 --> 00:59:18.408
"You could draw
me to the gallows.

555
00:59:18.533 --> 00:59:20.744
"You could draw me to any death.

556
00:59:20.827 --> 00:59:23.455
"You could draw me to
anything I've most avoided.

557
00:59:23.538 --> 00:59:26.750
"This and the confusion
of my thoughts.

558
00:59:26.833 --> 00:59:30.086
"So that time fit for
nothing is what I mean

559
00:59:30.211 --> 00:59:33.840
"by your being the ruin of me."

560
00:59:33.923 --> 00:59:37.677
Why'd you stop?

561
00:59:37.761 --> 00:59:40.013
We should go.

562
00:59:46.269 --> 00:59:50.315
Hey! What are you
doing here? Stop!

563
01:00:48.373 --> 01:00:51.501
Perhaps the most
mesmerizing of all things

564
01:00:51.626 --> 01:00:54.504
is the binary star couple.

565
01:00:54.587 --> 01:00:58.341
Two stars find their way
across vast stretches of space

566
01:00:58.466 --> 01:01:01.428
and time to find
another wandering body

567
01:01:01.553 --> 01:01:05.473
and become attached for
eternity in each others' orbit.

568
01:01:05.557 --> 01:01:11.479
Each star pushing the other
to explode in supernova...

569
01:01:16.651 --> 01:01:19.863
becoming either the
nucleus of planetary nebula

570
01:01:19.988 --> 01:01:23.742
or just as often,
resulting in a death spiral.

571
01:01:23.867 --> 01:01:28.872
What are you doing,
Tessa? Learning about the stars?

572
01:01:28.955 --> 01:01:34.169
The stars assist
in each others' system.

573
01:01:34.252 --> 01:01:38.923
Do you have any idea
how beautiful you are right now?

574
01:01:45.388 --> 01:01:47.849
What are you always
writing in there?

575
01:01:47.932 --> 01:01:49.768
None of your business.

576
01:01:59.110 --> 01:02:01.112
- Show me.
- No.

577
01:02:03.073 --> 01:02:05.075
- Come on!
- No chance!

578
01:02:05.158 --> 01:02:06.868
I just want to see what's...

579
01:03:13.184 --> 01:03:15.478
Tessa, hun?

580
01:03:15.603 --> 01:03:17.063
I've called all the... Tessa?

581
01:03:17.147 --> 01:03:20.608
Mom? What are you doing here?

582
01:03:20.692 --> 01:03:22.986
What the hell is going on?

583
01:03:23.111 --> 01:03:24.320
Nothing.

584
01:03:24.446 --> 01:03:26.740
Who's he? Is he the
guy Noah told me about?

585
01:03:26.823 --> 01:03:29.826
So this is how you spend your
time instead of going to class?

586
01:03:29.909 --> 01:03:31.286
No!
- I think I should go.

587
01:03:31.369 --> 01:03:32.537
You think?

588
01:03:32.662 --> 01:03:35.957
Can we talk about this
outside please? Please!

589
01:03:37.709 --> 01:03:40.003
You, go! Come with me.

590
01:03:44.632 --> 01:03:46.718
You have got to be kidding me.

591
01:03:46.843 --> 01:03:48.720
I knew as soon as I
saw that roommate

592
01:03:48.845 --> 01:03:50.138
that something like
this would happen.

593
01:03:50.221 --> 01:03:52.098
Are you serious right now?

594
01:03:52.182 --> 01:03:53.767
And after all this work

595
01:03:53.892 --> 01:03:57.437
and you are gonna throw
it away for some boy!

596
01:03:57.520 --> 01:03:59.522
What are you talking
about? I'm not.

597
01:04:01.066 --> 01:04:03.109
You're going to break
up with this boy

598
01:04:03.193 --> 01:04:06.696
and you are going to
focus on your schoolwork.

599
01:04:11.701 --> 01:04:13.870
Do you even know what it
has been like trying to be

600
01:04:13.953 --> 01:04:17.874
perfect for you,
having you mold my life

601
01:04:17.957 --> 01:04:20.668
into the way that
you wanted it to be?

602
01:04:20.752 --> 01:04:23.922
I did it for your own good.

603
01:04:24.005 --> 01:04:28.051
I am so, so sorry, Mom, that
your life didn't work out

604
01:04:28.176 --> 01:04:31.930
the way that you wanted
it to, I really am

605
01:04:32.055 --> 01:04:35.100
but this is my life and
you have to let me live it.

606
01:04:40.522 --> 01:04:43.233
Is that really what you want?

607
01:04:43.358 --> 01:04:45.568
Yes.

608
01:04:54.536 --> 01:05:00.125
If I leave now, you're cut off.

609
01:05:06.715 --> 01:05:09.050
He's gonna break your heart.

610
01:05:29.904 --> 01:05:32.490
She's cutting
you off because of Hardin.

611
01:05:32.615 --> 01:05:35.160
I'm just a little
worried, is all?

612
01:05:35.285 --> 01:05:37.454
Why?

613
01:05:37.537 --> 01:05:40.040
Hardin is...

614
01:05:40.165 --> 01:05:43.585
Hardin is complicated.

615
01:05:43.668 --> 01:05:48.048
Yeah, I know, but he's
different around me.

616
01:05:48.131 --> 01:05:50.091
Just be careful.

617
01:06:04.314 --> 01:06:05.648
You okay?

618
01:06:05.732 --> 01:06:08.109
Yeah. Where have you been?

619
01:06:10.570 --> 01:06:13.698
Jump in and I'll show you.

620
01:06:20.455 --> 01:06:21.790
- You ready?
- Yes!

621
01:06:21.873 --> 01:06:24.125
- Are you sure?
- Yes!

622
01:06:30.757 --> 01:06:32.217
Who's place is this?

623
01:06:34.928 --> 01:06:39.349
A friend of my
father's, a professor.

624
01:06:39.474 --> 01:06:41.976
Where are they?

625
01:06:42.060 --> 01:06:48.066
She's in Italy. Oh yeah, I'm
meant to be watering the plants.

626
01:06:51.319 --> 01:06:52.904
Ooh, she paints.

627
01:07:00.870 --> 01:07:03.998
It's really nice.

628
01:07:07.585 --> 01:07:09.879
Imagine if it were our place.

629
01:07:09.963 --> 01:07:12.507
Sure.

630
01:07:12.590 --> 01:07:14.426
It can be.

631
01:07:16.219 --> 01:07:21.099
What, you mean,
like live together?

632
01:07:26.896 --> 01:07:28.898
When you told me your mom
was going to cut you off

633
01:07:28.982 --> 01:07:30.650
I had to do something.

634
01:07:30.734 --> 01:07:33.778
We can stay here for
the rest of the year

635
01:07:35.530 --> 01:07:36.948
just you and me.

636
01:07:43.246 --> 01:07:45.290
You did this for me?

637
01:08:09.856 --> 01:08:11.149
- Here.
- Mm-hm.

638
01:08:18.907 --> 01:08:20.992
You're gonna bring out
the best of our loves.

639
01:08:21.117 --> 01:08:21.951
Mm-hm.

640
01:08:27.290 --> 01:08:28.500
Whoa!

641
01:09:22.011 --> 01:09:24.889
Look at that one.
It looks a bit like you.

642
01:09:26.516 --> 01:09:29.978
This is crazy.

643
01:09:45.535 --> 01:09:47.954
I still can't believe it.

644
01:09:48.038 --> 01:09:49.873
Hm? Believe what?

645
01:09:52.375 --> 01:09:54.335
That you're mine.

646
01:09:56.671 --> 01:09:58.381
Not this again.

647
01:10:02.385 --> 01:10:04.262
I don't deserve you.

648
01:10:07.474 --> 01:10:12.854
Nothing could ever change the
way that I feel about you.

649
01:10:32.916 --> 01:10:35.001
- I can not believe you've
talked me into this.

650
01:10:35.085 --> 01:10:38.922
- It's a wedding reception,
it's not a jail sentence.

651
01:10:42.175 --> 01:10:43.218
Hey!

652
01:10:43.301 --> 01:10:45.178
- Hey, you guys made it.
- Yeah.

653
01:10:45.261 --> 01:10:48.139
- You look beautiful, Tessa.
- Oh, thank you.

654
01:10:48.264 --> 01:10:49.599
Hey, you clean up well, man.

655
01:10:50.767 --> 01:10:52.143
This is so fancy.

656
01:10:53.144 --> 01:10:54.938
Yeah, it's beautiful.

657
01:10:55.980 --> 01:10:57.440
So we're brothers.

658
01:10:59.442 --> 01:11:00.610
Yeah.

659
01:11:02.445 --> 01:11:05.448
You must be really happy
for your mom and Ken.

660
01:11:05.573 --> 01:11:07.992
Yeah, yeah, I am.

661
01:11:09.953 --> 01:11:11.955
I'll see you two in there.

662
01:11:19.921 --> 01:11:22.006
This looks so good.

663
01:11:38.148 --> 01:11:42.277
Look who's here.
It's good to see you.

664
01:11:42.360 --> 01:11:43.653
You, too.

665
01:11:43.737 --> 01:11:45.780
And you must be...
- Tessa.

666
01:11:45.864 --> 01:11:47.031
Tessa.
Tessa, I'm Karen.

667
01:11:47.157 --> 01:11:48.199
- Hi.
- I'm Landon's mom.

668
01:11:48.324 --> 01:11:49.868
- It's so nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

669
01:11:49.993 --> 01:11:51.619
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

670
01:11:53.163 --> 01:11:55.790
It means a lot to me
that you could be here.

671
01:11:55.874 --> 01:11:57.751
Congratulations.

672
01:11:57.834 --> 01:11:59.961
Thanks for coming.

673
01:12:00.837 --> 01:12:04.466
I'm happy you decided
to join us, son.

674
01:12:04.549 --> 01:12:06.718
Landon tells us you're in
Professor Soto's seminar.

675
01:12:06.843 --> 01:12:07.969
Yeah.

676
01:12:08.053 --> 01:12:10.138
So, you're an English major?

677
01:12:10.221 --> 01:12:13.641
Um, I would love to, but I think
if I want to be employed

678
01:12:13.725 --> 01:12:16.561
maybe business or econ.

679
01:12:16.686 --> 01:12:18.688
If you're interested in the
business side of literature

680
01:12:18.813 --> 01:12:20.815
my friend owns a
publishing company.

681
01:12:20.899 --> 01:12:22.776
You mean Vance?
- Yes.

682
01:12:22.859 --> 01:12:24.652
Well, I can call Vance for her.

683
01:12:24.736 --> 01:12:27.322
Of course, I'm sure he'd
be happy to hear from you.

684
01:12:29.324 --> 01:12:34.079
Ken, Dana's arrived.
I think we should go say hi.

685
01:12:35.997 --> 01:12:37.332
Enjoy.

686
01:12:38.875 --> 01:12:41.086
- Nice meeting you.
- Yeah, you too.

687
01:12:49.052 --> 01:12:51.805
Let's just have fun.

688
01:12:51.888 --> 01:12:54.557
I can't.

689
01:12:54.641 --> 01:12:57.310
Why not?

690
01:12:57.394 --> 01:13:00.230
You made me promise to
be on my best behavior.

691
01:13:34.806 --> 01:13:37.142
Thank you all for coming.

692
01:13:37.267 --> 01:13:40.937
Tonight we celebrate
great, good fortune

693
01:13:41.062 --> 01:13:44.399
and her name is Karen.

694
01:13:44.482 --> 01:13:48.236
The love of my life and...
and frankly she saved my life.

695
01:13:48.319 --> 01:13:53.700
I'm suddenly blessed by a
new bride, a new life and

696
01:13:53.783 --> 01:13:57.245
not one, but two
brilliant sons...

697
01:13:58.830 --> 01:14:01.624
Hardin and Landon.

698
01:14:04.169 --> 01:14:06.629
I remember an earlier time
when my greatest pleasure

699
01:14:06.755 --> 01:14:11.301
was to listen to Hardin,
who loved to recite passages

700
01:14:11.426 --> 01:14:13.386
from novels, all by memory

701
01:14:13.470 --> 01:14:17.015
and he would perform
them, leaving me with tears...

702
01:14:17.140 --> 01:14:19.768
He's not the man I grew up with.
- or laughter.

703
01:14:20.727 --> 01:14:24.147
My father was a drunk
and nothing more.

704
01:14:26.399 --> 01:14:30.070
At least he's trying

705
01:14:30.153 --> 01:14:32.489
which is more than
my father ever did.

706
01:14:35.200 --> 01:14:36.826
People change.

707
01:14:36.910 --> 01:14:40.997
Clearly, but that still
doesn't change what happened.

708
01:14:45.210 --> 01:14:47.712
What happened?

709
01:14:52.008 --> 01:14:54.219
One night, when I was eight

710
01:14:59.057 --> 01:15:02.644
my dad was at the pub,
drunk as usual.

711
01:15:03.853 --> 01:15:07.107
He messed with the wrong guys.

712
01:15:07.190 --> 01:15:09.651
They came to our
house for payback.

713
01:15:11.820 --> 01:15:13.321
He wasn't there.

714
01:15:16.199 --> 01:15:17.700
They found my mom instead.

715
01:15:20.704 --> 01:15:22.747
I tried...

716
01:15:27.752 --> 01:15:30.839
I tried to fight them
off, but I couldn't.

717
01:15:33.758 --> 01:15:38.680
Thank you, my friends, my
family and university faculty.

718
01:15:38.763 --> 01:15:43.727
And that's my dad, the
beloved Chancellor Scott.

719
01:15:44.477 --> 01:15:47.856
Let's have fun!

720
01:15:56.573 --> 01:16:00.827
I don't suppose you recall
any of those passages.

721
01:16:00.910 --> 01:16:05.331
Not the way you remember it.

722
01:16:05.415 --> 01:16:08.960
I would love to have a dance
with your brilliant son.

723
01:17:46.182 --> 01:17:47.892
I want you now.

724
01:18:30.477 --> 01:18:32.437
Are you sure?

725
01:18:34.147 --> 01:18:36.399
Yeah.

726
01:18:55.502 --> 01:18:57.420
Do you want me to stop?

727
01:18:59.839 --> 01:19:02.133
No, just go slow.

728
01:19:28.159 --> 01:19:29.953
- Car.
- It was "cat".

729
01:19:30.078 --> 01:19:31.746
Do another one.

730
01:19:38.461 --> 01:19:42.549
Uh-that one is...

731
01:19:44.509 --> 01:19:48.430
- I have no idea!
- I'm really good at this, yeah.

732
01:19:48.513 --> 01:19:51.015
Okay, just do one more,
I promise, I'll get it.

733
01:20:06.114 --> 01:20:08.366
Um...

734
01:20:20.336 --> 01:20:25.967
Hm I don't know, what was it?

735
01:20:45.403 --> 01:20:48.865
Can always stay up
late and work on that.

736
01:20:48.948 --> 01:20:50.742
- I'll just see you.
- I'll text you.

737
01:21:04.422 --> 01:21:06.049
Hey.

738
01:21:06.174 --> 01:21:07.884
Hey.

739
01:21:08.009 --> 01:21:10.095
How's it going? I haven't seen
you since like the bonfire.

740
01:21:11.554 --> 01:21:14.933
Yeah, I've been busy, I guess.

741
01:21:16.643 --> 01:21:19.229
How's it going with you
and your boyfriend?

742
01:21:20.647 --> 01:21:24.401
Uh, we're not together anymore.

743
01:21:24.526 --> 01:21:27.195
Ouch. Bye-bye, high school.

744
01:21:27.278 --> 01:21:28.905
Yeah, it was pretty painful.

745
01:21:29.030 --> 01:21:32.992
Yeah, I can tell you
moved on pretty quickly.

746
01:21:33.076 --> 01:21:34.411
How's Hardin?

747
01:21:34.536 --> 01:21:35.787
What do you mean?

748
01:21:35.912 --> 01:21:38.123
He told me you guys
have been hanging out.

749
01:21:38.248 --> 01:21:40.291
Yeah, we have.

750
01:21:42.001 --> 01:21:43.628
Cool.

751
01:21:45.088 --> 01:21:46.840
Really?

752
01:21:46.923 --> 01:21:51.136
Yeah, I mean Hardin
does what Hardin does.

753
01:22:35.138 --> 01:22:36.765
What's wrong?

754
01:22:37.849 --> 01:22:41.186
What's all this about?

755
01:22:41.311 --> 01:22:44.856
What didn't you tell me?

756
01:22:44.981 --> 01:22:46.649
Nothing. I don't know
what she's talking about.

757
01:22:46.775 --> 01:22:48.610
You don't know what
she's talking about?

758
01:22:48.693 --> 01:22:50.403
- I mean, I don't know.
- What didn't you tell me?

759
01:22:50.487 --> 01:22:51.362
Nothing.

760
01:22:53.448 --> 01:22:54.491
I need to go.

761
01:22:54.574 --> 01:22:57.911
What, now? Hardin, answer me!
Where are you going?

762
01:22:57.994 --> 01:22:59.871
- Out.
- What's going on?

763
01:23:03.333 --> 01:23:04.667
Do you trust me?

764
01:23:04.751 --> 01:23:05.794
Of course, I do, I just...

765
01:23:05.877 --> 01:23:07.212
Then what's the problem?

766
01:24:34.090 --> 01:24:35.800
What are you doing
in Hardin's car?

767
01:24:35.925 --> 01:24:38.303
What, I can't borrow his car?

768
01:24:40.764 --> 01:24:42.932
Jace, just tell me where he is!

769
01:24:45.977 --> 01:24:48.146
Maybe he's at Blind Bob's.

770
01:25:16.925 --> 01:25:20.845
Oh, my gosh, hey.
What's the matter?

771
01:25:23.848 --> 01:25:25.308
Are you okay?

772
01:25:25.392 --> 01:25:26.976
Yeah.

773
01:25:27.102 --> 01:25:29.813
You want some fries,
are you hungry?

774
01:25:29.938 --> 01:25:33.733
I haven't seen
you since you moved out.

775
01:25:33.817 --> 01:25:38.863
Um, I've been living
with Hardin off-campus.

776
01:25:38.988 --> 01:25:42.659
Wait, you two are
living together?

777
01:25:42.742 --> 01:25:43.910
Yeah.

778
01:25:43.993 --> 01:25:46.538
Wow, Tessa, I didn't know
you two were that serious.

779
01:25:46.663 --> 01:25:48.164
Yeah, we are.

780
01:25:48.289 --> 01:25:50.542
How long has
this been going on for?

781
01:25:50.667 --> 01:25:51.835
Look who I found.

782
01:25:51.918 --> 01:25:53.169
Oh, hey, Jace, hi, Hardin.

783
01:25:53.294 --> 01:25:55.672
- What's up? What's up, Tessa?
- You are very talented.

784
01:25:55.797 --> 01:25:57.716
I got you.

785
01:25:57.841 --> 01:25:59.175
Tessa?

786
01:26:01.177 --> 01:26:03.680
Hi, Hardin.

787
01:26:03.763 --> 01:26:06.349
Tessa was just
telling us the latest.

788
01:26:08.017 --> 01:26:10.979
Tessa's been filling us
in on all the details.

789
01:26:11.062 --> 01:26:12.147
Moving in together?

790
01:26:12.230 --> 01:26:15.191
And you guys are so adorable.

791
01:26:15.275 --> 01:26:18.528
Is there anything you
want to tell Tessa?

792
01:26:18.611 --> 01:26:21.197
Yeah, like what's been going
on between you and her?

793
01:26:21.281 --> 01:26:22.699
Nothing's going on
with me and her.

794
01:26:22.782 --> 01:26:24.868
Well, I don't believe you.

795
01:26:24.951 --> 01:26:26.202
What have you said?!

796
01:26:26.327 --> 01:26:29.039
- Tessa, I swear...
- I saw the texts that she sent.

797
01:26:29.164 --> 01:26:31.124
What te... they
didn't mean anything.

798
01:26:31.207 --> 01:26:32.500
I didn't even reply to
them, they meant nothing.

799
01:26:32.584 --> 01:26:35.045
- You're kidding me.
- Tessa, nothing's going on.

800
01:26:35.128 --> 01:26:37.338
Don't you think this thing
has gone a little too far?

801
01:26:37.422 --> 01:26:40.216
What thing, Hardin?

802
01:26:40.341 --> 01:26:44.220
Something's going on, but
it's not what you think.

803
01:26:44.304 --> 01:26:46.181
Molly, shut up.

804
01:26:49.059 --> 01:26:53.730
Tessa, let's get out of
here and I'll explain.

805
01:26:53.855 --> 01:26:56.107
I'll explain
everything, I promise.

806
01:26:56.232 --> 01:26:58.026
Remember truth or dare?

807
01:26:59.819 --> 01:27:01.821
What?

808
01:27:01.905 --> 01:27:03.365
Molly, don't.

809
01:27:05.909 --> 01:27:07.369
Molly!

810
01:27:08.745 --> 01:27:11.373
I'm done playing this game.

811
01:27:13.375 --> 01:27:15.210
- Oh!
- I like this girl.

812
01:27:15.293 --> 01:27:20.715
Looks like Hardin Scott
just got his first rejection.

813
01:27:20.799 --> 01:27:22.717
You don't think I
can make it happen?

814
01:27:22.801 --> 01:27:25.053
Make what
happen, Hardin?

815
01:27:25.136 --> 01:27:29.057
Here's a dare: make her
fall in love with me

816
01:27:29.140 --> 01:27:32.977
and then, I'll just...

817
01:27:35.438 --> 01:27:37.148
turn it off.

818
01:27:44.406 --> 01:27:46.408
It was all a game.

819
01:27:47.617 --> 01:27:53.164
Tessa, Tessa...

820
01:27:53.289 --> 01:27:55.458
Tessa, please you
have to believe me.

821
01:27:57.377 --> 01:27:59.963
Tessa, that was
before everything,

822
01:28:00.046 --> 01:28:03.133
before I got to know you.

823
01:28:08.763 --> 01:28:10.432
Is that true?

824
01:28:19.232 --> 01:28:21.526
And all of you knew?

825
01:28:30.744 --> 01:28:32.454
Tessa.

826
01:29:01.608 --> 01:29:04.360
Tessa, wait. Tessa!

827
01:29:04.444 --> 01:29:07.572
So, what exactly did
you tell them, then?

828
01:29:07.697 --> 01:29:09.074
Nothing.

829
01:29:11.159 --> 01:29:13.036
None of it was real.

830
01:29:14.621 --> 01:29:17.832
I actually thought...

831
01:29:17.916 --> 01:29:19.667
I thought that...

832
01:29:24.714 --> 01:29:27.133
You're just a liar.

833
01:29:27.217 --> 01:29:28.843
That was all before...

834
01:29:28.927 --> 01:29:30.470
Before what?

835
01:29:30.553 --> 01:29:31.971
Before...

836
01:29:32.055 --> 01:29:34.391
You snapped your fingers
and you turned it off.

837
01:29:41.398 --> 01:29:44.526
You said nothing could change
the way you felt about me.

838
01:29:47.946 --> 01:29:50.532
Then, I guess we're both liars.

839
01:31:37.889 --> 01:31:40.141
Hi, Mom.

840
01:31:59.202 --> 01:32:00.537
What happened?

841
01:32:03.331 --> 01:32:06.710
I don't really want
to talk about it.

842
01:32:11.589 --> 01:32:18.722
I just... I came here
to say that I'm sorry.

843
01:32:24.728 --> 01:32:28.857
I'm... I'm sorry, too.

844
01:32:32.068 --> 01:32:33.737
I love you.

845
01:33:06.978 --> 01:33:08.563
So how come you're back?

846
01:33:11.149 --> 01:33:13.318
I just needed to come home.

847
01:33:23.536 --> 01:33:25.622
I'm so sorry, Noah.

848
01:33:27.957 --> 01:33:30.335
I never meant to hurt you.

849
01:33:34.798 --> 01:33:36.800
Yeah, I know.

850
01:33:41.429 --> 01:33:46.768
I guess I just never
saw any of this coming.

851
01:33:49.479 --> 01:33:57.654
Yeah, but that's
like the point, right?

852
01:33:57.737 --> 01:34:02.325
We like... we change and
we discover who we are.

853
01:34:02.450 --> 01:34:05.286
I think that's okay.

854
01:34:06.746 --> 01:34:08.123
Yeah?

855
01:34:08.206 --> 01:34:09.624
Yeah.

856
01:36:26.010 --> 01:36:30.473
On a parting note,
I was deeply impressed by all

857
01:36:30.557 --> 01:36:33.935
of your papers attacking our
themes for this semester.

858
01:36:34.018 --> 01:36:37.188
Congratulations on
all of your good work.

859
01:36:49.034 --> 01:36:50.744
Miss Young?

860
01:36:54.205 --> 01:36:56.875
This is what Hardin turned in.

861
01:36:57.000 --> 01:37:01.129
I think it was actually written
more for you than it was for me.

862
01:37:08.136 --> 01:37:11.347
Thank you.

863
01:37:41.669 --> 01:37:43.838
What is that?

864
01:37:45.715 --> 01:37:51.054
Oh, a secret spot, and
a good place to think.

865
01:38:01.481 --> 01:38:04.359
I've read
hundreds of novels in my life.

866
01:38:04.442 --> 01:38:08.697
Most of them claiming that love
was the center of the universe.

867
01:38:08.780 --> 01:38:11.741
That it could heal any
damage inside of us.

868
01:38:11.825 --> 01:38:14.244
That it was what
we need to survive.

869
01:38:19.249 --> 01:38:22.919
From Darcy to Heathcliff,
I thought they were fools.

870
01:38:23.044 --> 01:38:25.213
That love was
something fictional

871
01:38:25.296 --> 01:38:29.342
only found in worn
pages of a book.

872
01:38:29.426 --> 01:38:33.430
But that has all changed since
I met my Elizabeth Bennet.

873
01:38:38.101 --> 01:38:40.854
I never thought I would
find myself completely

874
01:38:40.937 --> 01:38:45.108
and utterly consumed
by another until her.

875
01:38:45.233 --> 01:38:49.320
She took my hand and led
me out of the darkness

876
01:38:49.446 --> 01:38:52.282
and showed me that whatever
our souls are made of

877
01:38:54.951 --> 01:38:58.204
hers and mine are the same.

878
01:39:03.126 --> 01:39:08.256
I'm sorry. Please forgive me.

879
01:39:10.467 --> 01:39:13.470
You once asked who I
loved most in this world.

880
01:39:23.188 --> 01:39:25.315
It's you.

881
01:39:37.494 --> 01:39:42.457
WorldSrc

